Youths in Kebbi State under the aegis of Arewa Youths For Women And Good Governance has commended the minister of Justice and Attorney-General of the Federation Abubakar Chika Malami for bringing soccour to the people of Kebbi state at a time when food and other items needed for survival are hard to come by. The commendation was given in Birnin Kebbi by the state coordinator of Arewa youths for women and good governance honourable Abubakar Muhammad Fake. According to him, the association is none political but it is the ideology of the youth body to identify with anything good from anybody hence the reason to applaud him to encourage him to do more and for others to emulate him. He added that their concerns as youths are to help youths to grow and become useful to the society and Malami has become a vehicle through which youths propel and progress, his words â€œlet me state here without micing words that no fewer than 576 youths secured jobs at different federal ministries and parastatals across the country courtesy of Malami and at least 17 senior officers became heads of various government agencies all from Kebbi state, therefore we must commend him as youths body in Kebbi. He explained that in addition to jobs creations the minister has built a good number of jobs creating places like schools and other businesses that are providing jobs for the youths, while for political reasons he is being criticised we the youths are making headways through his good efforts. On the sidelines, the state coordinator also mentioned one Kabiru Labbo Jega who crashed the prices of rice, sugar and other consumables to ease the suffering of people in the state. He urged youths in the state to be law-abiding, stop drug addiction and refused to be used as political thugs reminding them their future is in their hands. POLL Recall that on Saturday, Malami had distributed rice, sugar and millet to the 21 local governments across the state as Ramadan palliatives.